-- South African Drives 32-Times Over Alcohol Limit, With 15 Sheep, Sapa Says
-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-12-24T06:12:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-24/south-african-drives-32-times-over-alcohol-limit-with-15-sheep-sapa-says.html
An unidentified South African
motorist was arrested in the Eastern Cape province after tests
showed he was driving while 32-times above the country’s legal
alcohol limit, the South African Press Association reported.  Also travelling in the motorist’s vehicle were five boys, a
woman and 15 sheep that may have come from nearby farms, the
news agency said, citing the department of transport. The woman
and the boys were also arrested, Sapa said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Renee Bonorchis  in Johannesburg at 
